      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions (Euler-Bernoulli beam bending, Hertzian contact) solved to within 1% of analytical result using the same element types and solver settings as the pedicle screw model.",
      "rationale": "Three canonical benchmark cases executed: cantilever beam bending, thick-walled cylinder under internal pressure, and Hertzian contact between two spheres. All results within 0.8% of analytical solutions. Code verification documented in internal report NVR-2024-003."
